    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Music in which sound is generated, transferred, triggered, or amplified by electronic devices. The creation of electronic music may involve the use of magnetic tape or digital technology and whose reproduction involves the use of loudspeakers. For works created with only natural sound sources recorded and manipulated via discs or magnetic tape use "musique concrète." For music created entirely through the use of a computer, in which the sound is initiated purely through digital means, use "computer music."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000017621/Sadie, New Grove Dictionary of Music and Musicians (1980)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046893/New Grove Dictionary of Music and Musicians (2001)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Muziek waarbij de klank door middel van elektronische apparatuur wordt opgewekt, overgebracht, geactiveerd of versterkt. Bij het maken van elektronische muziek kunnen magneetbanden of computers worden gebruikt. Gebruik 'musique concrète' voor werken die uitsluitend met behulp van natuurlijke geluidsbronnen worden opgenomen en bewerkt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>由電子儀器所產生、轉換、觸發或增強的音樂。創作電子音樂時可能同時使用磁帶或電腦。若為僅錄下自然聲源，並透過唱片或磁帶來操控變化的作品，則稱之為「具象音樂」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Música na qual o som é gerado, transferido, acionado ou amplificado por dispositivos eletrônicos. A criação de música eletrônica pode envolver o uso de fita magnética ou tecnologia digital e cuja reprodução envolve o uso de alto-falantes. Para obras criadas apenas com fontes sonoras naturais gravadas e manipuladas em discos ou fitas magnéticas, use "musique concrète". Para música criada inteiramente por meio do uso de um computador, na qual o som é iniciado exclusivamente por meios digitais, use "música de computador".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
